name: difss2d
params: class c0, class c1, class c2, wff w0

stmt.origin: syl(w0, wss(c0, c1), wss(c0, cdif(c1, c2)))

body.origin:
|- wi(w0, wss(c0, c1))
-| wi(w0, wss(c0, cdif(c1, c2)))
-| wi(wss(c0, cdif(c1, c2)), wss(c0, c1))

cumulated.origin:
|- wi(w0, wss(c0, c1))
-| wi(w0, wss(c0, cdif(c1, c2)))
-| wi(wss(c0, cdif(c1, c2)), wss(c0, c1))

|- wi(w0, wss(c0, c1))
-| wi(w0, wss(c0, cdif(c1, c2)))

comment: If a class is contained in a difference, it is contained in the minuend. Deduction form of ~ difss2 . (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)
